rComments: Prof. Harrison was a great prof, a little unclear about expectations but turned out to be a great challenge. He focuses on teaching you the arguments and expects you to get the data from the readings, so make sure you do them.

Dr. Harrison knows evvvverything about Near Eastern ceramics. He's super approachable and helpful, the work load was completely reasonable, but tests are based mostly on the text book so not doing the readings really isn't an option. Students in NMC should take as many classes with him as possible, he is an amazing teacher and resource.
